### Refresh Token API Test Cases
### POST /api/auth/refresh
### 
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code
### 
### Instructions:
### 1. First, login to get a refresh token
### 2. Replace the refreshToken value below with the actual token
### 3. Click "Send Request"

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@contentType = application/json

### ✅ Test 1: Valid Refresh Token
### Note: Replace with actual refresh token from login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "refreshToken": "REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_REFRESH_TOKEN"
}

### ❌ Test 2: Invalid Refresh Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "refreshToken": "invalid.token.here"
}

### ❌ Test 3: Missing Refresh Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
}

### ❌ Test 4: Empty Refresh Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "refreshToken": ""
}

